{
  "doc_id": "45779",
  "text": "Marked visceral obesity and extreme insulin resistance are associated with early-onset type 2 diabetes. The prevalence of diabetes is predicted to more than double to 366 million by 2030 [CITATION_1] . A more recent trend has been the shift of type 2 diabetes to middle-aged and younger populations. The new epidemic of obesity and type 2 diabetes in young people is becoming a clinical and health economic priority [CITATION_2] .",
